<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay, I revoke my argument.

260
00:11:53.519 --> 00:11:54.179
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Right.

261
00:11:54.179 --> 00:12:10.860
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, if you're going to do it in the permanent thing and be like, I think if you're going to do AI generated images, go all in, make it a point, tell people you're doing it, and then, and then you can, if you're convinced that people don't care, prove it, right?

262
00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:05.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

263
00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:17.639
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like say we're using AI generated images and we're doing it deliberately and then we'll see what happens whether people continue to buy it or not, right?

264
00:12:17.639 --> 00:12:22.019
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I think this is the thing is like most of the time, I actually saw an interesting video about this.

265
00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:19.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

266
00:12:22.019 --> 00:12:28.620
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Most people, when they get caught, if you will, with AI generated images.

267
00:12:28.620 --> 00:12:38.759
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I know that word is obviously whatever, but when people find AI generated images, they will always go something like, oh, it was just a placeholder and we forgot to fix that.

268
00:12:38.759 --> 00:12:39.539
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We changed that one.

269
00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:41.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: easy way out.

270
00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:45.120
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah, it's the easy way out and it's like, well, okay, what if there's other ones we've missed?

271
00:12:45.120 --> 00:12:46.259
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Right?

272
00:12:46.259 --> 00:12:47.100
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, how do we know?

273
00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:47.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Sure enough.

274
00:12:47.100 --> 00:12:54.000
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, But like, just if you if you think it's okay, just see it, right?

275
00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:55.559
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like just say, yeah, no, we did it.

276
00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:55.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Stand behind it.

277
00:12:55.559 --> 00:12:56.879
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We don't care, right?

278
00:12:56.879 --> 00:12:57.659
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, yeah.

279
00:12:57.659 --> 00:12:59.519
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Do it or don't do it.

280
00:12:59.519 --> 00:13:05.940
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And I just like the whole idea of the placeholder of things is it makes it harder to notice placeholder images when they're realistic looking.

281
00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:07.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: That's true too.

282
00:13:06.720 --> 00:13:13.799
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So if you really care about these images not getting out, you do a stupid, you go into paint, you draw a stick figure, you put that in.

283
00:13:13.799 --> 00:13:15.720
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: That's a placeholder image, right?

284
00:13:15.720 --> 00:13:21.720
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: A realistic looking Over the top AI generated image is not a placeholder image.

285
00:13:21.720 --> 00:13:27.299
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And I cannot be convinced that anyone is legitimately wanting to use them as placeholder images.

286
00:13:26.460 --> 00:13:28.139
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: It's true.

287
00:13:27.299 --> 00:13:28.500
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I just can't.

288
00:13:28.139 --> 00:13:32.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: You could just draw your little stick figure and then dump out 20 litres of water and you've done the same thing.

289
00:13:31.500 --> 00:13:34.620
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah.

290
00:13:34.620 --> 00:13:36.539
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Anyway, rant over.

291
00:13:36.539 --> 00:13:39.360
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Uh, I'm not going to tell you to not play the game.

292
00:13:39.360 --> 00:13:43.440
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I will tell you, they're using AI generated images and they're not telling you they're doing that.

293
00:13:43.440 --> 00:13:44.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: That's what I'm.

294
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:44.720
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Hmm.

295
00:13:44.720 --> 00:13:45.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

296
00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:49.860
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So, sadly, that's one episode I won't be doing.

297
00:13:49.860 --> 00:13:51.720
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I'm not saying I won't cover the game in the future.

298
00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:58.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I don't know how I feel about that, but I'm certainly not covering the demo in this state. It's in just now with...

299
00:13:57.000 --> 00:14:00.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No, so was it far into the game that you found it or?

300
00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:07.740
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I was maybe like an hour in, so it wasn't too bad, but I think I think this is the thing is I...

301
00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:03.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

302
00:14:07.740 --> 00:14:12.659
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It's I don't want to be one of those people that says, oh, well, everything has AI.

303
00:14:12.659 --> 00:14:15.960
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Everything's going to end up having AI, so why bother fighting it, right?

304
00:14:15.960 --> 00:14:17.519
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And I'm also not this

305
00:14:16.500 --> 00:14:17.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No.

306
00:14:17.519 --> 00:14:23.879
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: also not the sort of person that says that all, um, all LLM based stuff is wrong.

307
00:14:23.879 --> 00:14:25.620
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I don't believe that personally.

308
00:14:25.620 --> 00:14:32.879
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Uh, I definitely use some in my coding because it makes specific things that I do much quicker.

309
00:14:32.879 --> 00:14:38.460
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: What I do have a problem with is the maximalizing, we're going to use it for everything.

310
00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.799
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I don't like it being used for art, just in general.

311
00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:41.460
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No.

312
00:14:40.919 --> 00:14:43.139
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I think that that's silly.

313
00:14:41.460 --> 00:14:43.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Exactly.

314
00:14:43.620 --> 00:14:52.799
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And I think I can kind of see the argument of like, oh, I'm an indie developer, I can't do everything and I don't have the money to do these things.

315
00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:45.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yes.

316
00:14:52.799 --> 00:14:53.879
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I'm not saying it's okay.

317
00:14:53.879 --> 00:14:56.759
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I can see the argument, but here's a thing.

318
00:14:55.500 --> 00:14:56.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yes.

319
00:14:56.759 --> 00:15:00.779
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Why are you making a game? If you don't want to make art.

320
00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:02.019
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Well, that's it.

321
00:15:02.019 --> 00:15:06.519
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: You're supposed to use AI to do to regular things in your life so you can make the art yourself.

322
00:15:06.500 --> 00:15:08.240
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah.

323
00:15:06.519 --> 00:15:09.340
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Not use AI for the art.

324
00:15:08.779 --> 00:15:18.139
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah, yeah, it's, it, it, I don't, I don't, if you, if you don't want to make any of the art for a game.

325
00:15:09.820 --> 00:15:12.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No, that's totally.

326
00:15:18.139 --> 00:15:22.700
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: You're essentially just writing a physics engine.

327
00:15:22.700 --> 00:15:25.220
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And that's the boring bit, right?

328
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:26.139
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: true, it's true.

329
00:15:25.220 --> 00:15:28.580
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, that's the bit we pay other companies to do for us.

330
00:15:28.580 --> 00:15:30.559
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, I don't know.

331
00:15:29.500 --> 00:15:30.039
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Exactly.

332
00:15:30.039 --> 00:15:32.980
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: I think of the reason people even love art games.

333
00:15:30.559 --> 00:15:32.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I don't know what.

334
00:15:32.980 --> 00:15:34.480
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Sorry, I'm cutting you off here.

335
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: No, no go for it.

336
00:15:34.480 --> 00:15:37.299
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: The reason people love games so much.

337
00:15:37.299 --> 00:15:41.679
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: It could have the most basic playing formula, but if you love the art, a lot of people will stick with that.

338
00:15:41.679 --> 00:15:43.840
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: And I don't find the opposite to be true.

339
00:15:43.840 --> 00:15:50.320
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Like if the game is fun or if the art, sorry, if the game is great, but the art looks bad, people may not be as interested.

340
00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:54.059
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah, yeah, I think I think it probably depends on who you are.

341
00:15:54.059 --> 00:15:59.039
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But yeah, like I just, I just feel like if you're, if you don't care about how your game looks.

342
00:15:59.039 --> 00:16:01.860
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I don't understand why you're making a game, right?

343
00:16:01.860 --> 00:16:08.940
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, there are, there are so many arguments for like, I don't like doing this part of this job, and so therefore I will automate this part of this job.

344
00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:02.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah, that's.

345
00:16:08.940 --> 00:16:17.759
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: There are very many legitimate reasons for that in so many jobs, but like, what's the core point of your job, right?

346
00:16:13.500 --> 00:16:14.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Mm-hmm.

347
00:16:17.759 --> 00:16:21.600
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It's like, it's like with, with, let's go back to my job programming, right?

348
00:16:21.600 --> 00:16:24.779
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like I quite often use AI to like check that.

349
00:16:24.779 --> 00:16:37.559
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It's really good at like finding, you know, tiny bugs that I've missed or it's really good at like noticing the specific testing that I've missed out or it's really good at me going, I have absolutely no idea what the issue is with here.

350
00:16:37.559 --> 00:16:42.419
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Can you, you know, see if you can figure out something I'm missing.

351
00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:45.779
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It's really good for those things, things that humans are really bad at, right?

352
00:16:45.779 --> 00:16:49.740
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like humans are really bad at tiny minute details.

353
00:16:49.740 --> 00:16:52.559
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Ironically, the thing it's really bad at in images.

354
00:16:52.740 --> 00:16:54.419
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But,

355
00:16:53.500 --> 00:16:54.879
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah, fair.

356
00:16:54.480 --> 00:17:05.880
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But like, I don't understand why the developers, right, I understand why normal people will be doing this because they want to make their own software and not do the coding.

357
00:17:05.880 --> 00:17:10.019
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But I don't understand, and this is happening all over the industry and it's driving me insane.

358
00:17:10.019 --> 00:17:15.240
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I don't understand why developers are vibe coding, why they're going, I don't want to do the coding anymore.

359
00:17:15.240 --> 00:17:17.519
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I just want to talk to the computer and tell it what to do.

360
00:17:17.519 --> 00:17:20.640
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Your job is decoding.

361
00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:18.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Right.

362
00:17:21.500 --> 00:17:22.039
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yep.

363
00:17:22.039 --> 00:17:24.200
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: This is what you, yeah, exactly.

364
00:17:23.640 --> 00:17:24.960
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Right?

365
00:17:24.200 --> 00:17:25.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: So.

366
00:17:24.960 --> 00:17:28.980
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, I, I, I, I can, it's different if you're talking about a societal level, right?

367
00:17:28.980 --> 00:17:31.680
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like say, let's talk about like self-driving cars.

368
00:17:31.680 --> 00:17:38.759
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I personally think the self-driving cars overall will be better in at some point, hopefully, than human drivers.

369
00:17:38.759 --> 00:17:43.559
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And I think that when we get to that point, we should probably stop driving as humans because they'll be better than us and less people will die.

370
00:17:43.559 --> 00:17:47.640
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: If I was a taxi driver, I wouldn't be doing that myself.

371
00:17:44.500 --> 00:17:45.400
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yes.

372
00:17:48.059 --> 00:17:49.559
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Right?

373
00:17:48.400 --> 00:17:52.299
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Kick back and just join them on the ride.

374
00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:52.779
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Exactly.

375
00:17:52.420 --> 00:17:54.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

376
00:17:52.779 --> 00:17:54.700
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, there's a massive difference there.

377
00:17:54.700 --> 00:17:58.000
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like don't don't automate yourself out of the job.

378
00:17:57.859 --> 00:18:00.619
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Don't make yourself obsolete.

379
00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:02.980
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It's just, it's absolutely bizarre to me.

380
00:18:02.980 --> 00:18:05.200
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, I want to make a game, but I don't want to make any art.

381
00:18:05.200 --> 00:18:06.700
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I don't know why you're making the game.

382
00:18:07.500 --> 00:18:15.539
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: And you think about it too, when people start with, if they have, like, an idea for a game in their head, the 1st thing they want to do, typically, from what I've seen is they want to make the art.

383
00:18:15.539 --> 00:18:16.859
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: They want to draw out their characters.

