00:39:02.500 --> 00:39:15.460
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, I just, yeah, because I think one of the things about life, I'm going to say as a non-verbal person, I am not a non-verbal person, but obviously I have to speak for my non-verbal child because he can't.

814
00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:14.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yes.

815
00:39:15.460 --> 00:39:21.820
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I guess a thing about being a non-verbal person is you're quite often the only non-verbal person around.

816
00:39:21.500 --> 00:39:22.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Right, exactly.

817
00:39:21.820 --> 00:39:29.500
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Obviously not in certain circumstances because like he goes to a school with lots of people who need help in different ways.

818
00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:31.119
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And so obviously there he is surrounded.

819
00:39:31.119 --> 00:39:34.179
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But like in day to day other life, right?

