<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1382
01:12:41.880 --> 01:12:43.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

1383
01:12:42.979 --> 01:12:57.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah, I think I might need to try him with this game and see what he thinks because he loves playing games like he's into Mario and Astrobot and a whole bunch of other games, Minecraft.

1384
01:12:56.500 --> 01:12:57.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Nice.

1385
01:13:00.500 --> 01:13:04.520
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So I'd love to get. What?

1386
01:13:00.500 --> 01:13:05.479
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: I imagine all of our kids are nerdy. With who our with who their parents are.

1387
01:13:05.899 --> 01:13:07.502
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Never.

1388
01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:12.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Um, how is your your younger son?

1389
01:13:13.000 --> 01:13:14.560
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Oh, that's an interesting question.

1390
01:13:14.500 --> 01:13:16.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: If you don't mind me asking.

1391
01:13:14.560 --> 01:13:17.380
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: No, no, no, no, absolutely.

1392
01:13:17.380 --> 01:13:18.640
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I said I was going to be open.

1393
01:13:18.640 --> 01:13:22.479
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: They have an interesting relationship.

1394
01:13:22.479 --> 01:13:28.180
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I mean, they're never going to have, you know, normal sibling relationship, whatever that means.

1395
01:13:28.600 --> 01:13:42.819
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, I think certainly when he was younger trying to explain that Nathan doesn't talk was difficult and, you know, we're going through that with his cousins just know as well, his younger cousins, his older cousin.

1396
01:13:41.500 --> 01:13:42.399
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1397
01:13:42.819 --> 01:13:47.199
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: He has he has 2 older cousins and then he has 3 younger cousins.

1398
01:13:47.199 --> 01:13:51.460
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, and the 3 younger cousins are 3, 2, and 0.

1399
01:13:51.460 --> 01:14:02.500
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And so we're just kind of getting to the point where the oldest is starting to notice that Nathan doesn't actually talk because I think at some point you just don't at certain ages you just don't notice it, right?

1400
01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:52.960
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1401
01:14:02.500 --> 01:14:07.359
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: You're just like, people exist and I don't really notice the difference between people.

1402
01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:04.260
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Right, yeah.

1403
01:14:04.260 --> 01:14:05.760
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

1404
01:14:07.359 --> 01:14:13.239
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, But yeah, it's it's a difficult thing to kind of explain to another child.

1405
01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:08.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No.

1406
01:14:13.239 --> 01:14:24.520
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I mean, when we obviously experience it quite a lot when Nathan's out and about playing and like a child comes up to and tries to engage him in conversation and it's like, you don't want to immediately go in and say, oh, he doesn't talk, right?

1407
01:14:24.520 --> 01:14:29.439
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: You don't want to remove the kind of interaction that's happening, but also Nathan just ignores them.

1408
01:14:28.000 --> 01:14:28.960
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Right.

1409
01:14:29.439 --> 01:14:33.340
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like he doesn't generally care about other children.

1410
01:14:33.399 --> 01:14:35.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I think.

1411
01:14:33.500 --> 01:14:34.159
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1412
01:14:34.159 --> 01:14:37.699
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah, I don't want to like immediately say, oh, just don't bother.

1413
01:14:37.500 --> 01:14:38.520
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Exactly, exactly.

1414
01:14:37.699 --> 01:14:40.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: It just, oh, he communicates in a different way.

1415
01:14:38.520 --> 01:14:40.140
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: You don't want to.

1416
01:14:40.140 --> 01:14:42.060
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Exactly, because who knows one day he might.

1417
01:14:42.060 --> 01:14:48.779
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: One day he might start interacting with children and I don't want to like stop it when it's about to happen and then I never would have known that that would have happened.

1418
01:14:48.779 --> 01:14:51.539
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It hasn't happened yet, but that doesn't mean it won't.

1419
01:14:51.539 --> 01:14:57.060
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But at some point you do have to go in and you have to be like, he doesn't, he doesn't talk.

1420
01:14:52.000 --> 01:14:53.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Oh exactly.

1421
01:14:57.060 --> 01:15:04.739
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Feel free to try and play with him, but the chances are he won't, you know, he won't play with you, but absolutely try.

1422
01:15:04.739 --> 01:15:06.239
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like there's nothing, nothing wrong with that.

1423
01:15:06.239 --> 01:15:08.279
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And as I say, like the kids at his school are great.

1424
01:15:08.279 --> 01:15:12.899
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: They've all learned a bunch of sign language, even though Nathan doesn't use.

1425
01:15:11.500 --> 01:15:12.579
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Oh, that's amazing.

1426
01:15:12.579 --> 01:15:13.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Oh.

1427
01:15:12.899 --> 01:15:19.439
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Nathan doesn't use sane language, but they've still learned it and they still use it with him just because, right?

1428
01:15:19.439 --> 01:15:20.699
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Because they're like, you never know.

1429
01:15:20.699 --> 01:15:23.880
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And I think it's it's so lovely the way they do that.

1430
01:15:23.880 --> 01:15:27.659
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But, um, different people understand him in different ways.

1431
01:15:24.500 --> 01:15:25.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: That's great.

1432
01:15:27.659 --> 01:15:39.359
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But yeah, Craig is, I think, I think Craig and Nathan treat each other the same way and that they just kind of exist nearby, right?

1433
01:15:39.359 --> 01:15:42.600
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like, and it's kind of, in a way, it's in a way, it's sad, right?

1434
01:15:40.000 --> 01:15:41.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay, swear it up.

1435
01:15:42.600 --> 01:15:48.119
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like because they don't have any sort of normal sibling relationship.

1436
01:15:48.500 --> 01:15:50.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No, it's a different dynamic.

1437
01:15:50.500 --> 01:16:13.000
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And like a lot of a lot of the thing with having a child who is likely to never develop in the same way that other people do and is likely to never, you know, he's never going to have, unless we don't stop trying, just to make this clear, I don't want people to think we've given up.

1438
01:16:13.000 --> 01:16:15.819
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We absolutely have not given up and we are likely never to give up.

1439
01:16:13.500 --> 01:16:14.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No, no.

1440
01:16:15.819 --> 01:16:22.779
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But at this point, have he, you know, he's a living and he still doesn't have very basic communication.

1441
01:16:22.779 --> 01:16:29.079
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We've kind of got come to the realisation that he's never going to get to certain points.

1442
01:16:29.079 --> 01:16:36.819
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And that is a difficult thing to live with because in a way, it's a kind of grief, right?

1443
01:16:36.819 --> 01:16:46.779
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like you're, you, when you have a child, and I've experienced this in multiple ways, because we went through a couple of miscarriages as well.

1444
01:16:37.000 --> 01:16:38.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Absolutely.

1445
01:16:46.960 --> 01:16:49.479
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Nathan was actually meant to be a twin.

1446
01:16:49.479 --> 01:16:56.800
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, we uh, went to the 1st scan and there were 2 and then the 2nd scan, there was only one.

1447
01:16:50.500 --> 01:16:51.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Oh.

1448
01:16:56.800 --> 01:17:02.380
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And so we've experienced this sort of thing in multiple different ways.

1449
01:17:02.380 --> 01:17:11.680
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But yeah, when you become a parent and you'll, you'll know this, like you have expectations and you have, like, you know what, you know what having a child is, right?

1450
01:17:11.680 --> 01:17:23.380
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: You have a child and they are a baby and then they're a toddler and then they learn to be themselves and then they grow up and they become an adult and they move away and and that is the natural progression of things, of having a child.

1451
01:17:14.500 --> 01:17:15.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yep.

1452
01:17:23.000 --> 01:17:31.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Well, it's that you have sentimental milestones that you're expecting to achieve with them and then, yeah, it's absolutely something that you grieve.

1453
01:17:29.000 --> 01:17:30.380
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And then,

1454
01:17:30.380 --> 01:17:33.020
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And then you never experience them.

1455
01:17:33.560 --> 01:17:42.439
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, you know?

1456
01:17:35.500 --> 01:17:37.840
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: This is a hard episode for you to start me off.

1457
01:17:38.319 --> 01:17:41.319
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: People are like, never bring this girl back.

1458
01:17:42.739 --> 01:17:44.840
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Uh, I don't know.

1459
01:17:44.840 --> 01:17:46.760
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I cried on the Spirit Fader episode as well.

1460
01:17:47.420 --> 01:17:50.479
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So, I don't know what my point is.

1461
01:17:52.500 --> 01:17:59.579
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No, but people say like, oh, it's a blessing to have a child that has like, is disabled.

1462
01:17:59.579 --> 01:18:14.880
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: It's like, well, you know, you love them no matter why, but there is still the expectation, like, of hope of, I don't want to say a normal childhood, but like you have a child with the hope of reaching certain parts of life together and experiencing life with your child.

1463
01:18:14.939 --> 01:18:19.380
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: And, you know, I would not try to sound.

1464
01:18:19.380 --> 01:18:23.340
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Bad at all anyway, but uh, that's just what you would expect.

1465
01:18:23.340 --> 01:18:27.180
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Like, people get, for example, people.

1466
01:18:27.180 --> 01:18:32.039
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Uh, get a dog with the expectation of, oh yeah, I can take my dog up for a walk.

1467
01:18:32.039 --> 01:18:54.359
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: I can feed my dog, I can play with my dog, but then if you get a dog that's reactive or like, gets injured, it's a different experience, and obviously I'm not comparing paranoid to dog ownership, but like, you get something, you plan for something in your life with the expectation of it going a certain way, and you do grieve if that doesn't happen the way that you had planned on it.

1468
01:18:54.359 --> 01:18:56.819
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: If I'm explaining that at all correctly.

1469
01:18:54.500 --> 01:18:55.220
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah.

1470
01:18:55.579 --> 01:18:58.760
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: No, no, yeah, yeah, no, you are.

1471
01:18:58.760 --> 01:19:02.300
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: I mean, for me, you are, but like.

1472
01:19:00.500 --> 01:19:01.279
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah, no.

1473
01:19:01.279 --> 01:19:10.039
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Again, I do not speak for everyone on the planet, but from my own experience, and from what I've seen as a healthcare employee.

1474
01:19:10.039 --> 01:19:20.239
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Like I see children that, you know, Never walk, never feed themselves, and, you know, the parents will pull me aside just because that's my job.

1475
01:19:20.239 --> 01:19:22.520
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: And I see the disappointment.

1476
01:19:22.520 --> 01:19:27.680
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: I see the grief and they have no one else to talk to, so they often will tell me like this isn't what we expected.

1477
01:19:27.680 --> 01:19:30.500
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Am I a bad person for wanting something else?

1478
01:19:30.500 --> 01:19:32.239
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: And then you say, of course not.

1479
01:19:32.239 --> 01:19:40.039
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: And it's just maybe a taboo situation, but like I understand 100% expecting a different reality.

1480
01:19:40.500 --> 01:19:45.840
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah, I think day to day, it's, uh, it's not something you think about too deeply, right?

1481
01:19:45.840 --> 01:19:48.659
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Because then you'd just be constantly depressed.

1482
01:19:46.500 --> 01:19:47.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No.

1483
01:19:49.079 --> 01:19:52.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But, you know, it's something.

1484
01:19:50.000 --> 01:19:50.720
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

1485
01:19:54.000 --> 01:19:56.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: From time to time.

1486
01:19:56.000 --> 01:19:56.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Of course.

1487
01:19:58.500 --> 01:19:59.399
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Still love him.

1488
01:19:59.399 --> 01:20:01.260
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: He's an absolutely adorable child.

1489
01:20:01.260 --> 01:20:02.460
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: That helps.

1490
01:20:02.500 --> 01:20:03.579
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: That helps.

1491
01:20:03.579 --> 01:20:04.119
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

1492
01:20:04.119 --> 01:20:07.600
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Nature knew what it was doing, making the kids cute.

1493
01:20:07.500 --> 01:20:14.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: But yeah, um, he's, we've actually, so interestingly, around his uh, communication board.

1494
01:20:16.000 --> 01:20:29.140
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: started off very simply with him, because obviously, as I mentioned, it's not like, unlike the child in this game, can't just be told a word given a symbol and then immediately has that connection.

1495
01:20:29.140 --> 01:20:35.680
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We took literally years to get to the point where he could use even one symbol.

1496
01:20:30.000 --> 01:20:30.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No.

1497
01:20:35.500 --> 01:20:36.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Wow.

1498
01:20:35.739 --> 01:20:41.920
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, and uh, anyone who knows Nathan will know that it was a food symbol.

1499
01:20:41.920 --> 01:20:43.060
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It was snack.

1500
01:20:43.060 --> 01:20:44.260
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It was, I want a snack.

1501
01:20:43.500 --> 01:20:44.520
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Perfect.

1502
01:20:44.560 --> 01:20:47.140
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: He is very food driven.

