<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Do you work with, um, is it like an occupational therapist or?

1556
01:23:37.500 --> 01:23:40.680
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Oh, we have a 1000000000 people that we work with.

1557
01:23:40.680 --> 01:23:46.319
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We have a ball, uh, we have, on the one hand, so much help.

1558
01:23:46.319 --> 01:23:57.720
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, his, so his 2 schools, his mainstream local school that he goes to for one day a week and his um, uh, specialist department in another school further away.

1559
01:23:57.720 --> 01:24:01.319
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Everyone that he works with in both of those is absolutely amazing.

1560
01:24:01.319 --> 01:24:03.300
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Like they go above and beyond.

1561
01:24:02.500 --> 01:24:03.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: That's.

1562
01:24:03.300 --> 01:24:06.060
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We just, we couldn't ask for for better people.

1563
01:24:06.420 --> 01:24:12.239
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, and a lot of the health professionals that we work with, they're also really good.

