01:24:24.720 --> 01:24:27.119
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: as with all systems.

1569
01:24:25.000 --> 01:24:25.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1570
01:24:27.119 --> 01:24:29.460
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: There's always going to be problems.

1571
01:24:29.460 --> 01:24:34.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And then some of them, I wonder why they're in the...

1572
01:24:34.500 --> 01:24:36.960
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Oh, that's the worst part.

1573
01:24:37.500 --> 01:24:45.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So I'm struggling to remember the specifics of which person is which, so I can't remember what an occupational therapist does.

1574
01:24:45.500 --> 01:24:51.920
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay, so they, they can do the communication book, but it could also be speech language pathologist.

1575
01:24:51.920 --> 01:24:55.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Well, in Ontario anyway, so the occupational therapist would...

1576
01:24:57.000 --> 01:24:58.439
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: I can't even explain it.

1577
01:24:59.000 --> 01:25:10.640
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So we've, we've had, we've had speech, we've had speech therapy dealing with him, but they, um, they, they came to the conclusion that they can't help him based on his, like how he is.

1578
01:24:59.340 --> 01:25:01.260
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Certain.

1579
01:25:01.800 --> 01:25:03.479
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

1580
01:25:10.640 --> 01:25:16.039
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, so I think part that's part of the problem is that he's he's not unique.

1581
01:25:11.000 --> 01:25:12.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1582
01:25:16.039 --> 01:25:25.159
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: There are people like him, but his lack of understanding is so severe that so many people don't know what to do with him.

1583
01:25:25.500 --> 01:25:26.520
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay, yeah.

1584
01:25:26.520 --> 01:25:31.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: There has to be like a certain baseline to build upon for.

1585
01:25:29.500 --> 01:25:31.060
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Exactly, exactly.

1586
01:25:31.060 --> 01:25:36.100
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And I think the problem is that because there's so few people like Nathan, they don't know what to do.

1587
01:25:36.100 --> 01:25:47.502
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: You know, it's like, okay, well, we can't, like these buckets that we have for throwing people into and helping them, he doesn't fit into any of these buckets, so we don't really know where to put it.

1588
01:25:48.000 --> 01:25:48.539
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1589
01:25:48.539 --> 01:25:52.319
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: So yeah, like in Ontario, um, they would do adoptive equipment.

1590
01:25:52.319 --> 01:25:59.939
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: So like wheelchairs, um, ramps, like anything that would help, like, with increased safety in the house.

1591
01:25:59.939 --> 01:26:04.439
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Um, I don't know if you've had any of, of that or?

1592
01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:09.239
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah, I mean, obviously we don't need many kind of physical adjustments because he's physically, you know, fine.

1593
01:26:09.239 --> 01:26:11.399
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We've never had any issues with that.

1594
01:26:10.000 --> 01:26:10.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah.

1595
01:26:11.399 --> 01:26:23.819
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: We have had a couple of adaptations in the house, but it's because so we got a wet room put in because he would get completely over the top in the bath and he just completely flooded our house.

1596
01:26:23.000 --> 01:26:23.960
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Oh.

1597
01:26:23.819 --> 01:26:27.180
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So we ended up getting a wet room in and that was a huge thing.

1598
01:26:27.180 --> 01:26:29.279
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So we got funding for that and we got help with that.

1599
01:26:28.500 --> 01:26:29.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1600
01:26:29.279 --> 01:26:35.039
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So, yeah, we do have, I think mostly it's the social worker we work with to get that sort of stuff.

1601
01:26:35.039 --> 01:26:37.680
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: He's the one that kind of goes and gets budgets for things.

1602
01:26:37.680 --> 01:26:44.699
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So we have like, um, this really has just turned into just talking about life.

1603
01:26:38.000 --> 01:26:38.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1604
01:26:44.699 --> 01:26:48.119
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: So I think we're probably done with talking about the game.

1605
01:26:48.119 --> 01:26:53.100
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: if you, if you, if you don't want to hear about personal stuff, then you, you, you can go now.

1606
01:26:53.100 --> 01:27:00.479
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, We get like some respite care and stuff like that.

1607
01:27:00.479 --> 01:27:04.439
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Not enough, but that's always the case with these things, right?

1608
01:27:01.000 --> 01:27:01.502
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Okay.

1609
01:27:03.500 --> 01:27:04.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: No.

1610
01:27:04.439 --> 01:27:08.520
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: And they, I mean, his caterers are great.

1611
01:27:08.520 --> 01:27:11.880
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: They're fantastic, but budgets only stretch so far.

1612
01:27:09.500 --> 01:27:10.579
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Oh, that's great.

1613
01:27:11.239 --> 01:27:18.739
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Yeah, I have, when I was doing home care, I would do respite care for some clients and I felt like I barely saw them.

1614
01:27:18.739 --> 01:27:22.279
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: Just because of how far they're, they're funding would stretch.

1615
01:27:19.500 --> 01:27:20.002
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah.

1616
01:27:22.500 --> 01:27:23.502
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

1617
01:27:22.819 --> 01:27:27.002
<v 75AE8ACE-FE15-4280-8B00-188C37215357>Chelsea: And no, seems like it's a universal problem, unfortunately.

1618
01:27:27.500 --> 01:27:28.340
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It really is.

1619
01:27:28.340 --> 01:27:29.300
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: It really is.

1620
01:27:29.300 --> 01:27:42.979
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Um, uh, I don't I don't think there is a system that fixes everything with, because I think part of the problem is that these needs can be so complex and, uh, you know, without infinite money.

1621
01:27:42.979 --> 01:27:45.439
<v AF2CBEBB-3493-475E-82E9-7A7A0C03AAF3>Al: Hey, if only there was a person with infinite money.

